🇺🇸Project K-9 Hero Adoption Opportunity🇺🇸

Our Project K-9 Hero Rehabilitation and Rehoming Facility is at 100% capacity, but that is not going to stop us from helping find this retired Police K-9 a fur-ever family!

Please meet K-9 Shadow, who served as a Dual-Purpose Patrol/Narcotics Detection K-9 with a large Police Agency in Arizona. He had a productive career removing criminals, drugs, and firearms from the streets, until his handler was assigned to a new position within the department. Since then he has been living there in retirement, until a recent bite incident with another member of the household has led to him needing to be rehomed. 

Yesterday, K-9 Shadow had an appointment to be euthanized due to the lack of resources or options available locally to rehome him. We are honored that our partners at @k9sofvalor, reached out to Project K-9 Hero, once they learned about this situation, so together we can help find Shadow the right situation within our thorough adoption process and vast network.

K-9 Shadow turned nine years old last October, and is a strong/high-drive Dutch Shepherd. He will require frequent attention and exercise, and can be strategically managed with the “right” owner who understands the proper way to handle him. Even though he may be retired, Shadow will need a very consistent schedule and routine. 

Shadow has been known to show aggressive tendencies when not given a job or a purpose. The incident that led to his unwarranted bite in the home was due to resource guarding over food. Shadow can be aggressive towards other animals, and is not recommended to be around small children. His current routine is staying in an indoor or outdoor kennel (roofed) with a run. 

If you are interested in giving K-9 Shadow a fur-ever home, please SEE THE COMMENTS FOR REQUIREMENTS!

If you feel you meet each and every one of these requirements listed, please complete and submit our adoption application at: LINK IN BIO

Meet Chancho! We are looking to help him find his forever home! Originally from Tijuana, MX, where he lost one of his eyes. Chancho is a very happy, high-energy, medium-drive dog who enjoys playing ball or tug, has a minimal foundational start into scent/detection work (as another outlet), has been good with dog-neutral dogs, and previously lived with another male with no issues. He has completed a board and train with us and is currently housed by us. There is no rehoming fee, and you will receive training with us for Chancho! 

Chancho does have the potential to make poor decisions at times with his teeth in specific circumstances. During his original board and train and his current stay with us, we have been unable to recreate this behavior. He will require a home with no small children willing to provide structure, exercise, and mental stimulation. Chancho is a special pup who needs a family that understands him. Applicants will be interviewed, and a home check is required.

If you're interested in learning more, reach out today at 602-677-7175.

Write a caption Yesterday, Project K-9 Hero was advised of an emergency situation to help save the life of retired Military Working Dog (MWD) "Claire" (R516). She was rushed to the ER with a Gastric Dilatation and Volvulus (GDV). Minus the immediate assistance of our nonprofit, it was clear that Claire had no chance of survival. 

Without hesitation, her admittance was approved, as soon as it was submitted by her handler, who was out of state on a work assignment. MWD Claire’s packet jumped right to the top of our over 700 pending program applications, due to her extreme special medical needs, and the financial burden of this procedure.

PK9H paid a total of $4,126.39 at the first Veterinary ER to get her stabilized. To perform the life-saving surgery, MWD Claire had to be transported to a secondary Veterinary ER, where we paid $10,449.93. A total of $14,576.32 in just a few hours last night to give this highly decorated Combat Veteran a fighting chance!

Sadly, when she finally got to the operating table the surgeon could not reverse the damage that had been done. MWD Claire crossed the rainbow bridge just prior to midnight on October 18th.

MWD Claire spent eight years assigned to the U.S. Army's 525th Military Working Dog Detachment in Wiesbaden, Germany. This extremely brave Hero was certified as a Patrol/Explosive Detection Dog that had an exemplary service record during her career. 

Claire deployed in support of combat operations in Eastern Afghanistan 🇦🇫, and Kosovo 🇽🇰. MWD Claire was assigned to the Special Response Team, and assisted the United States Secret Service to conduct explosive detection sweeps for the President of the United States and other dignitaries on over 25 missions. 

Please take a moment to say goodbye to MWD Claire posthumously, as Project K-9 Hero Program Member #256. We tried our absolute best to save you! PK9H will never let you be forgotten! - #JJK9
